{
  "id": 5176907844943872,
  "name": "Navigation API: add post-commit handler from precommit",
  "summary": "Currently when intercepting navigations with the `navigate` event, precommitHandlers and post-commit ordinary handlers are passed separately.\n\nThis works well when there is only one or the other, but can be a bit clunky when the flow includes a precommitHandler that leads to a post-commit handler.\n\nThis addition is a small ergonomic improvement that enables registering a post-commit handler while invoking a precommit handler.",
